{{Short description|American philosopher, scholar, philosopher, author, and activist}}
'''Januarius Jingwa (JJ) Asongu''' is a [[Cameroonian nationality law|Cameroonian]]-[[United States nationality law|American]] prolific writer, academic, [[Entrepreneurship|entrepreneur]], and [[Human Rights Activists in Iran|human rights activist.]]<ref>{{cite web |title=JJ Asongu - Google Scholar Citations |url=https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=FE8EXpQAAAAJ&hl=en |accessdate=2017-04-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author=Bahru Zewde |title=Society, State and Identity in African History: Bahru Zewde: 9789994450251: Amazon.com: Books |publisher=African Books Collective |year=2008 |isbn=978-9994450251}}</ref>

<ref name="eTurbo">eTurboNews (2021). "M12 set to sponsor the Ai4 2021 Cybersecurity Summit Startup Stage." [News Article].</ref>

<ref name="ISACA">ISACA (2020). "Africa CACS 2020: Featured Speakers - Januarius Jingwa Asongu." [Conference Program].</ref>

He is a prolific writer who has written on various subjects including business, cybersecurity, politics, psychology, philosophy, theology etc.

